[94mWe need to create space in the output. There are different ways to achieve this depending on the layout of your setup but some usual methods:
- Use inserters to move items from the output side of the miner to a near transport belt that takes it away (the transport belt could be a chained one that look like an "S" and goes back into the mining area and then outwards)
- Use long-handed inserters to directly place items from the output to another output, such as a chest or a furnace
- Move your output over so that the items don't interfere with the operations of the mining drill.
